-- Steyn Takes 11 Wickets as South Africa Beats Pakistan in Test
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2013-02-04T11:40:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-04/steyn-takes-11-wickets-as-south-africa-beats-pakistan-in-test.html
Dale Steyn  took 11-60 in the match as
South Africa beat Pakistan by 211 runs in the first cricket Test
in Johannesburg.  Steyn had figures of 5-52 as Pakistan totaled 268 in its
second innings, with captain Misbah-ul-Haq top scorer on 64. The
visitors had collapsed to 49 all out in the first innings, with
Steyn taking 6-8.  South Africa scored 253 and 275-3 declared, wicketkeeper AB
de Villiers making 103 not out in the second innings and taking
11 catches in the match.  The hosts completed victory before lunch on the fourth day.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Peter-Joseph Hegarty in London at 
 phegarty@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editors responsible for this story:
 Christopher Elser  at   celser@bloomberg.net . 